                <head>299. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On December 24, <gloss target="#t_EOKA1">EOKA</gloss> announced a unilateral
                    truce in its campaign of terrorism against the British authorities on Cyprus.
                    The <gloss target="#t_EOKA1">EOKA</gloss> action was a response to the request
                    of Archbishop <persName>Makarios</persName> to allow negotiations on the Cyprus
                    question to proceed in an atmosphere free from violence. The British Government
                    responded on December 30 by commuting four death sentences imposed on <gloss
                        target="#t_EOKA1">EOKA</gloss> terrorists.</p>
            </div>
